      <memberdef kind="function" id="classFastElim_1a590fb2ef34751a0c2dc550a5652e5e9f" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void FastElim::buildBackwardSub</definition>
        <argsstring>(vector&lt; unsigned int &gt; &amp;diag, vector&lt; Triplet&lt; double &gt; &gt; &amp;bops, vector&lt; double &gt; &amp;diagVal)</argsstring>
        <name>buildBackwardSub</name>
        <qualifiedname>FastElim::buildBackwardSub</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>vector&lt; unsigned int &gt; &amp;</type>
          <declname>diag</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>vector&lt; <ref refid="classTriplet" kindref="compound">Triplet</ref>&lt; double &gt; &gt; &amp;</type>
          <declname>bops</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>vector&lt; double &gt; &amp;</type>
          <declname>diagVal</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Operations to be done on the RHS for the back sub are generated and put into the bops (backward ops) vector. col &gt; row here, row is the entry being operated on, and col is given by rowsToSub. offDiagVal is the value on the off-diagonal at row,col. diagVal is the value on the diagonal at [row][row]. RHS[row] = ( RHS[row] - offDiagVal * RHS[col] ) / diagVal </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
